<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-07-11T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-07-11T02:00:00-05:00" n="209" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d209">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894.20211 Tachibana, Itaru/29:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-07-11T16:00:00+09:00">July 11,
                                    1941—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received July 13—9:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>984. Department’s 377, July 7, 10 p.m., missionaries in Korea. An
                            official of the Foreign Office informed a member of my staff today that
                            if any of the missionaries declined to leave Korea when the offer is
                            made judicial proceedings would continue and judgment made according to
                            law; that if any were then sentenced the Korean judiciary could hardly
                            be expected to entertain appeals for clemency once having offered to
                            permit them to leave the country.</p>
                        <p>Sent to the Department via Shanghai.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>